---
import PageHero from "../../../components/PageHero.astro";
import SAGPLayout from "../../../layouts/SAGPLayout.astro";
---

<SAGPLayout title="Annual Conference | Society for Ancient Greek Philosophy">

<PageHero
  kicker="Annual Conference"
  title="The Society’s annual gathering of scholars."
  subtitle="Each year, SAGP brings scholars together for carefully curated sessions devoted to original research, rigorous discussion, and the continuing study of Ancient Greek philosophy."
  image="/assets/images/parthenon_night.jpg"
/>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>What is the Annual Conference?</h2>
  </div>
  <div>
    <p>
      The SAGP Annual Conference is one of the Society’s central scholarly
      activities. It gathers researchers working in Ancient Greek philosophy for
      thematic sessions, moderated panels, and sustained intellectual exchange.
    </p>
    <p>
      The conference reflects the Society’s commitment to serious scholarship,
      collegial discussion, and an international community of inquiry.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>How the conference works</h2>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Thematic sessions</h3>
      <p>
        Sessions are organized around shared philosophical themes, allowing
        multiple scholars to approach a common problem or tradition from
        different perspectives.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Moderated discussion</h3>
      <p>
        Each session is guided by a moderator, emphasizing conversation rather
        than isolated presentation.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>International participation</h3>
      <p>
        Online access and clear time-zone information help scholars participate
        across countries and continents.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>Current conference</h2>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Annual Conference 2025</h3>
    <p>
      The 2025 SAGP Annual Conference will be held November 15–16, 2025, via
      Zoom. Sessions include work on Plato, Aristotle, Presocratic ontology, and
      Stoic epistemology.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/events/annual-conference/2025/`}>View the 2025 program</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>Conference archive</h2>
  </div>
  <div>
    <p>
      SAGP’s conference tradition extends back to the Society’s earliest decades.
      Past conferences and newsletters preserve a record of the Society’s
      continuing scholarly conversation.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/events/annual-conference/2024/`}>Annual Conference 2024</a></li>
      <li><a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/events/annual-conference/archive/`}>Past Conferences & Archives</a></li>
    </ul>

    <div class="callout">
      The Annual Conference is not simply a yearly event. It is one recurring
      expression of the Society’s long-standing commitment to scholarly dialogue.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</SAGPLayout>
